document_title: What is stillbirth? Signs and causes of stillbirth
subsection_content:
Stillbirth or stillbirth is a condition in which the fetus stops developing after the 20th week of pregnancy and before the mother goes into labor. Stillbirths are classified according to the number of weeks of pregnancy:
From 20 to 27 weeks: early stillbirth; From 28 - 36 weeks: late stillbirth; After 37 weeks: full-term stillbirth
